                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18336</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-08T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul Garrett telegraphed yesterday: [Here follows telegram from Consul Garrett
                    of June 7, 1916, 5 p.m.]</p>
                <p>Investigate foregoing and report. Department fears activity of de la Rosa may
                    develop into border raids unless he and his followers are curbed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
